  "notes": "Standard Macedonian, codified 1945. South Slavic, closely related to Bulgarian. Analytic case system (lost inflection). Fixed antepenultimate stress (third-from-last syllable). Unique letters: ⟨ѕ⟩ = [dz], ⟨ѓ⟩ = [ɟ], ⟨ќ⟩ = [c]. Definite article suffixed in three forms: -от/-та/-то (definite), -ов/-ва/-во (proximal), -он/-на/-но (distal). ⟨љ⟩ = [ʎ], ⟨њ⟩ = [ɲ].",
